00:25:43,590 --> 00:25:45,940
{\an9}♪ Oh, how much longer? ♪

534
00:25:46,190 --> 00:25:49,280
{\an9}♪ I thought I was in love a couple of times before ♪

535
00:25:49,280 --> 00:25:50,820
{\an9}♪ With the girl next door ♪

536
00:25:52,330 --> 00:25:57,070
And I remember thinking, "This is the moment...

537
00:25:59,100 --> 00:26:00,950
that I know will be in my mind

538
00:26:00,950 --> 00:26:05,360
when I -- when I -- when I close my eyes to die."

539
00:26:10,250 --> 00:26:13,290
Only I thought - that she'd be sitting there, right next to me,

540
00:26:15,410 --> 00:26:17,530
and I'd hear her say it one more time.

541
00:26:24,420 --> 00:26:27,000
I lost my toy scalpel.

542
00:26:29,680 --> 00:26:31,870
The one that Steve gave me.

543
00:26:35,300 --> 00:26:36,700
Yeah, I figured that was the one.

544
00:26:36,700 --> 00:26:39,540
I have been looking for a whole day.

545
00:26:40,410 --> 00:26:42,710
I think it may be gone forever.

546
00:26:49,440 --> 00:26:51,630
Maybe I'll come here when you're dead.

547
00:26:53,840 --> 00:26:54,840
Okay.

548
00:26:59,400 --> 00:27:02,340
Are your memories - of your daughter enough for you?

549
00:27:05,170 --> 00:27:06,560
Not even close.

550
00:27:15,680 --> 00:27:17,410
Do you need me to listen to you anymore?

551
00:27:17,410 --> 00:27:18,780
No, Shaun, you should go.

552
00:27:18,780 --> 00:27:19,800
Okay.

553
00:27:29,350 --> 00:27:30,900
Not all the cultures are back.

554
00:27:30,910 --> 00:27:32,970
But since he's not responding to any antibiotics,

555
00:27:32,970 --> 00:27:34,020
we can rule out bacterial.

556
00:27:34,030 --> 00:27:35,660
It was never a great fit.

557
00:27:35,670 --> 00:27:37,330
It's a better fit than surgical error.

558
00:27:37,330 --> 00:27:39,730
What if it is bacterial but resistant to all --

559
00:27:39,730 --> 00:27:40,440
Then he's dead.

560
00:27:40,440 --> 00:27:43,310
What about Paroxysmal Nocturnal Hemoglobinuria?

561
00:27:43,340 --> 00:27:46,030
Pnh? The incidence - is literally one in a million.

562
00:27:46,120 --> 00:27:47,980
What's the odds of Murphy screwing up?

563
00:27:47,980 --> 00:27:48,840
I'd put them about that.

564
00:27:48,840 --> 00:27:50,390
No, it's not PNH.

565
00:27:50,390 --> 00:27:52,010
Caden had normal flow cytometry.

566
00:27:52,010 --> 00:27:55,410
Exotic snake venom can trigger consumptive coagulopathies.

567
00:27:55,410 --> 00:27:56,630
So can pre-eclampsia,

568
00:27:56,630 --> 00:27:59,140
but he's not pregnant and he wasn't charming snakes.

569
00:28:01,740 --> 00:28:04,330
Murphy, any thoughts here?

570
00:28:05,560 --> 00:28:07,260
It is kind of your ass on the line.

571
00:28:26,840 --> 00:28:30,050
I know why Caden has DIC.

572
00:28:32,090 --> 00:28:35,980
I squeezed the artery between two clamps.

573
00:28:35,980 --> 00:28:38,260
I must have ruptured the aortic wall,

574
00:28:38,260 --> 00:28:40,340
causing a pseudo-aneurysm.

575
00:28:40,340 --> 00:28:42,150
It was my mistake.

576
00:28:44,020 --> 00:28:45,420
And also...

577
00:28:47,970 --> 00:28:50,550
I have to make a bowel movement.

578
00:28:57,600 --> 00:28:58,530
He's lying.

579
00:28:59,420 --> 00:29:00,630
He's gonna puke.

580
00:29:02,320 --> 00:29:03,850
He's going to Glassman.

581
00:29:06,860 --> 00:29:10,540
I told Dr. Melendez I had to make a bowel movement.

582
00:29:10,670 --> 00:29:13,030
I think he believed me.

583
00:29:13,620 --> 00:29:14,670
Color me proud.

584
00:29:14,670 --> 00:29:16,990
I have the answer.

585
00:29:17,550 --> 00:29:20,100
Shaun, I hope you're referring to your patient,

586
00:29:20,110 --> 00:29:21,420
but due to the fact that you're here,

587
00:29:21,430 --> 00:29:22,650
pretending to be in the bathroom,

588
00:29:22,650 --> 00:29:24,910
- I kind of doubt that. - Yes, it's your answer.

589
00:29:24,910 --> 00:29:25,970
We already --

590
00:29:26,850 --> 00:29:28,800
We already have my answer, Shaun.

591
00:29:29,820 --> 00:29:31,760
We can't do a biopsy on you

592
00:29:31,760 --> 00:29:33,700
because of the arteries in the way,

593
00:29:33,880 --> 00:29:36,300
like the arteries in Caden's abdomen,

594
00:29:36,300 --> 00:29:38,630
but we can't move the arteries in your brain because --

595
00:29:38,640 --> 00:29:40,990
Why did we go to the carousel?

596
00:29:41,820 --> 00:29:43,930
Because you were sad.

597
00:29:43,980 --> 00:29:45,670
What didn't I want to do?

598
00:29:47,000 --> 00:29:49,360
Do you not know the answers to these questions?

599
00:29:49,360 --> 00:29:50,760
I do know the answers, Shaun.

600
00:29:50,760 --> 00:29:52,660
I don't think you know the answers to these questions.

601
00:29:52,660 --> 00:29:55,050
You're not hearing me. I'm dying.

602
00:29:55,050 --> 00:29:56,380
There's still hope.

603
00:29:58,160 --> 00:29:59,440
Shaun, look at me.

604
00:30:00,960 --> 00:30:02,180
Look at me, please.

605
00:30:05,270 --> 00:30:08,310
There is no hope for me.

606
00:30:09,350 --> 00:30:10,020
I mean, hope?

607
00:30:10,020 --> 00:30:12,030
What -- What -- What -- What is hope?

608
00:30:12,030 --> 00:30:14,260
You hope the 49ers find a defense.

609
00:30:14,260 --> 00:30:16,910
You hope the number 4 bus comes on time.

610
00:30:16,910 --> 00:30:19,060
Doesn't mean they magically learn how to tackle.

611
00:30:19,060 --> 00:30:22,210
Doesn't mean the bus driver suddenly drives faster.

612
00:30:23,810 --> 00:30:27,320
Hope is irrelevant for me.

613
00:30:27,380 --> 00:30:29,950
Hope is painful.

614
00:30:31,380 --> 00:30:34,200
I don't want to spend what's left of my life

615
00:30:34,200 --> 00:30:37,310
chasing my tail around in a circle.

616
00:30:39,090 --> 00:30:40,180
You understand?

617
00:30:46,860 --> 00:30:47,880
Okay.

618
00:30:51,230 --> 00:30:52,160
Okay.

619
00:31:06,490 --> 00:31:09,990
Your tumor is located at the base of your skull.

620
00:31:11,310 --> 00:31:16,120
An open cranial biopsy would tell us what's wrong.

621
00:31:16,570 --> 00:31:18,500
But there are blood vessels in the way.

622
00:31:18,510 --> 00:31:21,910
The biopsy would cause an aneurysm or a bleed.

623
00:31:23,030 --> 00:31:26,540
But if we go through your nasal cribriform plate,

624
00:31:26,810 --> 00:31:30,020
we can cross the tentorium on the contralateral side

625
00:31:30,030 --> 00:31:32,370
and avoid all those blood vessels.

626
00:31:34,950 --> 00:31:38,880
We can do a biopsy through your nose.

627
00:31:46,640 --> 00:31:48,800
You can't die, too.

628
00:31:56,250 --> 00:31:58,000
I have to throw up.

629
00:32:05,040 --> 00:32:07,140
So how do we do this? Do we file a report?

630
00:32:07,140 --> 00:32:08,370
Talk to Andrews personally?

631
00:32:08,370 --> 00:32:09,810
You want to report Shaun?

632
00:32:09,880 --> 00:32:12,680
I don't want to. I think we have to.

633
00:32:12,680 --> 00:32:13,840
No, you want to.

634
00:32:13,840 --> 00:32:16,300
And we'd certainly have to if our sole agenda

635
00:32:16,310 --> 00:32:17,500
would be to take down Shaun

636
00:32:17,500 --> 00:32:19,440
and to give you one less person to compete against.

637
00:32:19,440 --> 00:32:21,180
And certainly, we'd absolutely "Have to"

638
00:32:21,190 --> 00:32:24,340
cover up and bury a possible fatal medical error

639
00:32:24,340 --> 00:32:26,610
if our sole agenda was to protect a friend?

640
00:32:26,610 --> 00:32:29,900
Protocol would seem to favor the bitch over the friend.

641
00:32:29,900 --> 00:32:31,130
Thanks?

642
00:32:33,050 --> 00:32:34,830
I threw up.

643
00:32:37,480 --> 00:32:38,930
We have a duty to report errors

644
00:32:38,930 --> 00:32:40,460
so they won't happen again.

645
00:32:40,950 --> 00:32:42,610
The process saves lives.

646
00:32:42,610 --> 00:32:45,130
And exactly what errors are we trying to avoid a repeat of?

647
00:32:45,470 --> 00:32:47,850
You worried about the next time an autistic surgeon operates

648
00:32:47,860 --> 00:32:49,700
on a drugged-up frat kid after finding out his mentor

649
00:32:49,700 --> 00:32:51,220
is dying of brain cancer?

650
00:32:54,190 --> 00:32:56,250
Dr. Melendez told us, Shaun.

651
00:32:56,270 --> 00:32:57,670
We're really sorry.

652
00:32:58,500 --> 00:32:59,680
It's okay.

653
00:33:00,660 --> 00:33:02,170
It's okay.

654
00:33:02,170 --> 00:33:04,710
I think he's going to be okay.

655
00:33:05,560 --> 00:33:06,620
The protocol exists

656
00:33:06,620 --> 00:33:08,450
so that we don't ask questions like that.

657
00:33:08,450 --> 00:33:10,210
That seems like a bad idea.

658
00:33:10,240 --> 00:33:11,720
You trust your judgment.

659
00:33:11,720 --> 00:33:13,180
Do you trust Morgan's judgment?

660
00:33:13,190 --> 00:33:15,500
Do you trust the judgment of all the doctors in this building?

661
00:33:15,510 --> 00:33:17,600
If you can make judgment calls, so can they.

662
00:33:17,600 --> 00:33:19,140
That's why we need these rules.

663
00:33:19,140 --> 00:33:22,240
No, the protocol is fine for everyone in this building,

664
00:33:22,240 --> 00:33:23,540
except for Shaun.

665
00:33:23,550 --> 00:33:26,610
They'd reprimand any one of us, but they will fire him.

666
00:33:27,220 --> 00:33:28,160
Okay.

667
00:33:29,990 --> 00:33:30,980
We report it.

668
00:33:30,980 --> 00:33:32,010
We get the investigation,

669
00:33:32,010 --> 00:33:33,940
make sure nothing like this ever happens again.

670
00:33:35,660 --> 00:33:36,920
But we tell them I did it.

671
00:33:37,880 --> 00:33:40,330
They'd fire you, too.

672
00:33:41,430 --> 00:33:43,180
It's not a terrible idea.

673
00:33:43,180 --> 00:33:44,520
Jared's out the door either way.

674
00:33:44,520 --> 00:33:46,320
Can we get back to the medicine?

675
00:33:46,500 --> 00:33:47,890
Caden is still alive.

676
00:33:47,900 --> 00:33:49,140
If we can keep it that way,

677
00:33:49,140 --> 00:33:50,730
there won't be any review.

678
00:33:50,740 --> 00:33:52,410
Which means no one will be asking questions,

679
00:33:52,410 --> 00:33:53,850
and no one will have to give answers.

680
00:33:53,860 --> 00:33:55,090
It all goes away.

681
00:33:55,090 --> 00:33:57,350
If Caden dies, we tell the truth

682
00:33:57,350 --> 00:33:59,620
and we face the consequences together.

683
00:34:00,670 --> 00:34:01,700
No.

684
00:34:03,240 --> 00:34:04,150
No.

685
00:34:05,420 --> 00:34:09,020
I thought I'd found my toy scalpel.

686
00:34:12,230 --> 00:34:14,170
We need you to come back to the group, Murphy.

687
00:34:17,650 --> 00:34:19,680
Get me imaging on that pseudo-aneurysm.

688
00:34:32,450 --> 00:34:33,330
What's up?

689
00:34:33,470 --> 00:34:35,450
Do you still feel - the same way about Dr. Murphy

690
00:34:35,460 --> 00:34:36,490
as when he got here?

691
00:34:38,670 --> 00:34:43,270
Dr. Glassman gave us certain...assurances.

692
00:34:45,600 --> 00:34:47,740
"If Shaun proves - anything less than excellent,

693
00:34:47,740 --> 00:34:49,900
if Shaun doesn't live up to everything I know he can do,

694
00:34:49,900 --> 00:34:51,220
he will be immediately released,

695
00:34:51,220 --> 00:34:53,100
and I will resign my position

696
00:34:53,490 --> 00:34:55,110
as president of the hospital."

697
00:34:55,500 --> 00:34:56,750
And you wrote it down.

698
00:34:56,750 --> 00:34:58,530
I made sure it was in the minutes.

699
00:34:59,090 --> 00:35:01,480
Shaun has exceeded my expectations.

700
00:35:01,490 --> 00:35:03,310
Mine, as well, and?

701
00:35:04,390 --> 00:35:07,680
And my feelings about Dr. Glassman have not changed.

702
00:35:08,890 --> 00:35:09,830
Thank you.

703
00:35:16,110 --> 00:35:17,440
We need to cut him open.

704
00:35:17,440 --> 00:35:18,950
We cut him open and he dies.

705
00:35:18,960 --> 00:35:21,630
He'll bleed out before we can even get the artery exposed.

706
00:35:22,080 --> 00:35:24,590
If we don't cut him open, he dies.

707
00:35:27,160 --> 00:35:28,990
Don't cut him open.

708
00:35:29,000 --> 00:35:29,990
Murphy, if we don't --

709
00:35:29,990 --> 00:35:33,430
We should insert an endovascular graft

710
00:35:33,440 --> 00:35:35,460
through his leg instead.

711
00:35:35,700 --> 00:35:37,870
Fix it from the inside out.

712
00:35:37,870 --> 00:35:40,050
I've done that for large abdominal aorta dilations,

713
00:35:40,050 --> 00:35:42,880
but this is a lengthy dissecting pseudo-aneurysm.

714
00:35:42,880 --> 00:35:44,000
It's safer.

715
00:35:44,000 --> 00:35:45,560
The aortic wall is already compromised.

716
00:35:45,560 --> 00:35:46,900
Could rupture completely.

717
00:35:46,900 --> 00:35:49,840
Caden could die as soon as we deflate the balloon inside the graft.

718
00:35:49,840 --> 00:35:51,370
But doing nothing will kill him.

719
00:35:51,370 --> 00:35:52,560
Not definitely.

720
00:35:52,580 --> 00:35:55,150
There's still a chance Caden will simply come out of this

721
00:35:55,150 --> 00:35:56,570
without any surgical intervention.

722
00:35:56,570 --> 00:35:58,620
5%, 10% maybe.

723
00:35:58,630 --> 00:35:59,430
Not nothing.

724
00:35:59,430 --> 00:36:00,540
And we're doubling down on Shaun

725
00:36:00,540 --> 00:36:02,250
after we know he caused this problem.

726
00:36:02,250 --> 00:36:03,950
How's that gonna look at an M&M?

727
00:36:05,150 --> 00:36:06,610
I trust Shaun's idea.

728
00:36:07,970 --> 00:36:09,950
He makes mistakes no one else would make,

729
00:36:09,960 --> 00:36:13,730
but he also makes saves none of us would have ever thought of.

730
00:36:14,260 --> 00:36:15,450
Thank you.

731
00:36:15,540 --> 00:36:16,480
You're welcome.

732
00:36:16,800 --> 00:36:18,760
I still don't think you should be working here.

733
00:36:18,760 --> 00:36:20,610
I don't think the trade-off is worth it.

734
00:36:22,380 --> 00:36:24,130
Well, let's prep him for surgery.

735
00:36:28,070 --> 00:36:29,690
Pull the guide wire, Reznick.

736
00:36:35,220 --> 00:36:36,560
I'm passing in the graft.

737
00:36:39,450 --> 00:36:41,970
You're right over the pseudo-aneurysm now.

738
00:36:54,080 --> 00:36:56,520
Inflating the balloon to deploy the graft.

739
00:37:05,920 --> 00:37:06,910
Deflating.

740
00:37:06,910 --> 00:37:08,260
Can I do it?

741
00:37:10,320 --> 00:37:11,350
It's delicate.

742
00:37:11,810 --> 00:37:13,300
No, it's not.

743
00:37:14,910 --> 00:37:18,410
And it will either work or it won't work.

744
00:37:19,760 --> 00:37:21,790
If my idea is wrong,

745
00:37:21,790 --> 00:37:25,520
he'll die as soon - as we complete this next step.

746
00:37:27,510 --> 00:37:29,950
You shouldn't have to live with that.

747
00:37:35,040 --> 00:37:38,040
Everything that happens in this room is my responsibility.

748
00:37:41,750 --> 00:37:42,870
We'll do it together.

749
00:37:54,790 --> 00:37:55,850
Deflating.

750
00:38:22,990 --> 00:38:24,180
Nobody's going home.

751
00:38:26,170 --> 00:38:30,140
I am proud of this team and what we accomplished today.

752
00:38:31,700 --> 00:38:33,540
Drinks are on me at Harry Hopes.

753
00:38:34,490 --> 00:38:36,010
We're celebrating?

754
00:38:36,400 --> 00:38:38,770
Today was a disaster, and we got lucky.

755
00:38:40,280 --> 00:38:41,170
You're right.

756
00:38:42,010 --> 00:38:44,810
But when you get lucky, you celebrate.

757
00:38:45,360 --> 00:38:46,220
Let's go.

758
00:39:01,040 --> 00:39:02,730
At some point in your career,

759
00:39:02,770 --> 00:39:04,340
you're going to kill someone.

760
00:39:06,060 --> 00:39:08,370
And I hope for your sake there's a doctor out there

761
00:39:08,370 --> 00:39:10,140
who still believes in you when you do.

762
00:39:25,520 --> 00:39:27,650
It was there all along.

763
00:39:28,230 --> 00:39:31,420
I have to go drinking, but I wanted you to know --

764
00:39:34,080 --> 00:39:35,950
Is that from an IV?

765
00:39:38,100 --> 00:39:40,280
You did the biopsy.

766
00:39:41,280 --> 00:39:42,200
I did.

767
00:39:44,010 --> 00:39:46,250
I have a low-grade glioma.

768
00:39:46,470 --> 00:39:48,180
Not a GBM?

769
00:39:48,290 --> 00:39:50,010
I told you --

770
00:39:50,010 --> 00:39:51,960
Cancer, Shaun. It's still cancer.

771
00:39:52,750 --> 00:39:54,610
I have to undergo brain surgery,

772
00:39:54,610 --> 00:39:57,450
which is really scary because I'm not the one performing it.

773
00:39:57,450 --> 00:40:00,080
Five days a week - for six weeks of radiation,

774
00:40:00,080 --> 00:40:02,780
10 more weeks of chemotherapy.

775
00:40:02,900 --> 00:40:04,360
And then?

776
00:40:07,990 --> 00:40:08,990
And then...

777
00:40:09,800 --> 00:40:11,350
with a little luck...

778
00:40:12,050 --> 00:40:15,140
you and I can go to the Super Bowl next season.

779
00:40:28,480 --> 00:40:30,010
You're going to live.

780
00:40:32,200 --> 00:40:33,240
There's hope.

781
00:40:37,210 --> 00:40:39,360
Now go. Go have some fun with your friends.

782
00:40:39,750 --> 00:40:43,620
Yes. First I have to tell Dr. Andrews about the mistake I made.

783
00:40:43,620 --> 00:40:45,000
Shaun, y-you can't.

784
00:40:45,880 --> 00:40:49,740
Protocol is clear, and reporting saves lives.

785
00:40:49,740 --> 00:40:52,370
And I hear Caden is on the road to recovery,

786
00:40:52,370 --> 00:40:54,490
so your mistake couldn't have been too bad.

787
00:40:54,490 --> 00:40:55,890
No, I made a mistake.

788
00:40:55,890 --> 00:40:57,450
Shaun, I understand that.

789
00:40:57,450 --> 00:40:59,540
But Dr. Andrews will use this.

790
00:40:59,540 --> 00:41:00,970
And do you remember the commitment

791
00:41:00,970 --> 00:41:03,200
that Dr. Glassman made when you were hired?

792
00:41:03,200 --> 00:41:05,670
I promised you'd be excellent, right, Shaun?

793
00:41:05,670 --> 00:41:07,630
And you have been excellent.

794
00:41:08,760 --> 00:41:12,120
You can't give Dr. Andrews this excuse.

795
00:41:12,760 --> 00:41:15,580
I was not excellent.

796
00:41:15,580 --> 00:41:18,000
This time, I was bad.

797
00:41:19,730 --> 00:41:23,100
And surgeons have to be excellent every time.

798
00:41:23,400 --> 00:41:24,340
Right, Shaun?

799
00:41:26,160 --> 00:41:27,170
You agree with him?

800
00:41:27,170 --> 00:41:30,340
I'm not gonna ask him to lie to save my job.

801
00:41:32,370 --> 00:41:33,480
Don't do this.

802
00:41:36,390 --> 00:41:37,610
It's up to Shaun.

803
00:41:38,390 --> 00:41:39,850
I trust your judgment.

804
00:41:46,250 --> 00:41:48,350
I'm not doing this to hurt you.

805
00:41:48,930 --> 00:41:49,830
I know.

806
00:41:50,460 --> 00:41:52,180
We are friends.

807
00:41:52,470 --> 00:41:53,560
Yes, we are.

808
00:41:54,880 --> 00:41:56,000
I love you.

809
00:41:56,970 --> 00:41:58,670
I know. I love you, too.

810
00:42:02,070 --> 00:42:03,350
I love you more.

